		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=130528">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Marble Galleria" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Marble+Galleria">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Marble Galleria" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=63&FN=Enchanter&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1974859&TN=Illusions+nerf&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1974859&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I apologize if this topic has already been mentioned before.  I did a manual search (the "Search Forums" script being broken again) and didn't find anything on this topic, except for a small mention in Jynxy's thread.  I have a simple question/complain about a recent patch.</P><P>Recently, enchanters' Illusion line of spells was changed so that non-playable forms no longer affect your faction.  My initial reaction was that this was great -- now, for example, I could hunt in say, Earth Elemental form with the strength buff and not be KOS to the barbarian guards in Everfrost.  Or I could use Skeleton form when I'm low on food and water (I've heard that you don't need to eat or drink in this form, although I've never actually tested it out) without worrying about a wandering NPS turning me into a smear on the grass.  </P><P>Then I was on Faydwer (for some reason) and decided to finally get my lazy ass down to the brownie village to get my latest Mana spell.  Guess what I learned?  That's right, both Earth Elemental and Minor Illusion will get your ass killed down there now.  Minor Illusion, for Quellious's sake!  What's the point of this spell now if all NPCs see through it?  The Illusion spells were one of the enchanter's class-defining spells (at least until those potions showed up), and now they're mostly useless.  </P><P>That's the complaint part of my post.  The question part is this:  What was the thinking behind this change?  I have grouped with very few enchanters with any of my characters, so I don't know much about how others play this class.  Was there some kind of exploit going on using these illusions?  Minor Illusion was a necessity for soloing before, so I could med safely.  Now what good is it?  It's been reduced from a useful spell to a "fun" one, like Voice Graft.  </P><P>Gee, thanks Sony.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
