		<hr size="1">Sony nerf'ed the faction changes due to too much programming script being needed to keep it up, because as of Luclin EQ is loading tons of script everytime you log on a toon and it is unfair for everyone to wait an extra thirty seconds just so us enchanters could spend 5 minutes in our EQ career buying some spells from some tweeked out Wood elf Runts. Only Player races and druid wolf form remained uneffected, thats why your rogue masks still work. Secondly, your religion is a factor, and illusion faction works this way, my enchanter is a dark elf, when she goes Illusion High Elf she gets a faction BOOST the same amount which a newbie high elf starts out with, and then you get a Religous boost or subtraction, but if you are agnostic that doesn't apply. So after the boosts and subtractions are done a Dark Elf Agnostic Enchanter is indifferent to High Elf guards. But if she would have followed Innoruuk she should be dubious. Now lets say the Dark Elf enchanter went kamakazi on some high elf guards this will lower her faction so next time she turns into a High Elf she might be threatening or way apprehensive. I hope that helps some..</P><P>Extica 65 Enchanter ~ Xegony.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
